-- France Plans to Freeze Spending 2013-2015, Les Echos Reports
-- B y   J a m e s   K r a u s
-- 2012-06-25T19:27:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-25/france-plans-to-freeze-spending-2013-2015-les-echos-reports.html
France  plans to freeze spending for
three years from 2013 through 2015, excluding debt and pension
payments,  Les Echos  reported, citing a statement to the cabinet
by Prime Minister Jean-Marc Ayrault.  Spending is to be frozen in absolute terms without taking
into account inflation, the newspaper added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
James Kraus in London at 
